7 "§ 116-74.46. Recipient selection; use of grant funds; duration and conditions of grants;
8 reporting requirements.
9 (a) Selection. – After evaluation of grant applications pursuant to G.S. 116-74.45, the
10 Commission shall notify the Authority of its selection of the recipients of grants for each fiscal
11 year. The Commission shall select up to eight grant recipients to be operating operate a school
12 leader preparation program with grant funds for forgivable scholarship loans in any fiscal
13 year.year and up to two recipients for a grant of up to two hundred fifty thousand dollars
14 ($250,000) per recipient per fiscal year to develop innovative ways of training principals.
15 (b) Use of Funds. Grant Funds for Forgivable Scholarship Loans. – Each eligible entity
16 that receives grant funds for forgivable scholarship loans shall use those funds to carry out the
