19 (c) Duration and Conditions of Grants. – The Commission shall also notify the Authority
20 of its decisions on the duration and renewal of grants to eligible entities made in accordance with
21 the following:
22 (1) The duration of grants for forgivable scholarship loans shall be as follows:
23 a. Grants shall be no more than six years and no fewer than two years in
24 duration, unless the Commission finds early termination of a grant is
25 necessary due to noncompliance with grant terms.
26 b. The Commission may renew a grant based on compliance with the
27 grant terms and performance, including allowing the grantee to scale
28 up or replicate the successful program as provided in subdivision (3)
29 of this subsection.
30 (1a) The duration of grants for training development shall be for one year. The
31 Commission may renew a grant for training development, in its discretion, on
32 an annual basis.
33 …
34 (3) In evaluating performance for purposes of grant renewal and making its
35 renewal decisions to provide to the Authority, Authority pursuant to
36 subdivision (1) of this subsection, the Commission shall consider at least the
37 following:
38 …
39 (d) Reporting Requirements for Grant Recipients. – Recipients of grants shall participate
40 in all evaluation activities required by the Commission and submit an annual report to the
41 Commission with any information requested by the Commission. The recipients shall comply
42 with additional report requests made by the Commission. Whenever practicable and within a
43 reasonable amount of time, grant recipients shall also make all materials developed as part of the
44 program and with grant funds publicly available to contribute to the broader sharing of promising
45 practices. Materials shall not include personally identifiable information regarding individuals
46 involved or associated with the program, including, without limitation, applicants, participants,
47 supervisors, evaluators, faculty, and staff, without their prior written consent. The Commission
48 shall work with recipients, local school administrative units, and public schools, as needed, to
49 enable the collection, analysis, and evaluation of at least the following relevant data, data related
50 to grants for forgivable scholarship loans, within necessary privacy constraints:
51 (1) Student achievement in eligible schools.
