12 PART II. PRINCIPAL FELLOWS PROGRAM MAY USE ADMINISTRATIVE FUNDS
13 FOR STATEWIDE PROGRAMMING
14 SECTION 2. G.S. 116-74.41B reads as rewritten:
15 "§ 116-74.41B. The North Carolina Principal Fellows Trust Fund.
16 …
17 (b) Use of Monies in the Trust Fund. – The monies in the Trust Fund may be used only
18 for the purposes set forth in this subsection, including the award of grants pursuant to
19 G.S. 116-74.44, administrative costs, and costs associated with Program operations in
20 accordance with this Article. The Authority may use up to two percent (2%) of the funds
21 appropriated for the Program or one hundred sixty thousand dollars ($160,000) from the Trust
22 Fund, whichever is greater, each fiscal year for administrative costs, including recovery of funds
23 advanced under the Program, and may allocate to the Commission up to eight hundred thousand
24 dollars ($800,000) from the Trust Fund each fiscal year for the following:
25 (1) The salary and benefits of the director and staff of the Program.
26 (2) The expenses of the Commission to administer the Program.
27 (3) Program monitoring and evaluation.
28 (4) Extracurricular enhancement activities for the Program.
29 (5) Repealed by Session Laws 2019-60, s. 1(y), effective July 1, 2021.
30 (6) Programming on research-based school leadership practices to be shared with
31 eligible entities in order to improve principal preparation throughout the State.
32 (c) Remaining Funds. – If at the end of each fiscal year there are funds remaining in the
33 Trust Fund that are not obligated or otherwise encumbered for another purpose, upon the request
34 of the Commission, the Authority shall allocate the funds to the Commission for any of the
35 purposes identified in subdivisions (3) through (6) of subsection (b) of this section."
36
37 PART III. EFFECTIVE DATE
38 SECTION 3. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025.
